They stone her, Fred.

01:47.333 --> 01:49.367
You reading one
of Shirley's stories?

01:49.369 --> 01:52.670
The whole town,
even her own children.

01:52.672 --> 01:54.338
They all stone her.

01:54.340 --> 01:57.508
That's creepy.

01:57.510 --> 01:59.446
It's terrific.

02:34.347 --> 02:36.079
♪ I'm in town ♪

02:36.081 --> 02:37.515
♪ Can't you hear me, honey? ♪

02:37.517 --> 02:40.116
♪ I'm in town ♪

02:40.118 --> 02:41.752
♪ Hanging 'round ♪

02:41.754 --> 02:44.390
♪ Just waiting for you ♪

02:45.825 --> 02:47.792
♪ Can't you see ♪

02:47.794 --> 02:51.462
♪ You're the one
and only one for me ♪

03:03.443 --> 03:05.308
♪ I confess ♪

03:05.310 --> 03:09.312
♪ I just can't live
without your kisses ♪

03:09.314 --> 03:11.248
♪ But I'm gonna say ♪

03:11.250 --> 03:14.685
♪ Ain't nobody gonna
bring me down ♪

03:40.413 --> 03:42.279
Oh!

03:42.281 --> 03:44.649
Moving target, bonus points!

03:46.519 --> 03:48.653
- That looks delicious.
- Oh, thank you.

03:51.624 --> 03:54.725
Oh!

03:54.727 --> 03:59.497
Welcome to our hallow end
of the Earth, my boy!

03:59.499 --> 04:01.766
Welcome to Bennington!

04:01.768 --> 04:03.334
Good to see you, Professor.

04:03.336 --> 04:05.235
Oh, look at this!
Ya, ya, ya, ya, ya.

04:05.237 --> 04:09.340
And, oh, who is
this lovely dove?

04:09.342 --> 04:11.174
Rose Nemser.
You must be Professor Hyman.

04:11.176 --> 04:14.311
Oh, Stanley.
Stanley.

04:14.313 --> 04:16.414
I profess nothing.

04:16.416 --> 04:18.248
Come, come, come, come.

04:18.250 --> 04:20.584
Let's get you watered down.

04:20.587 --> 04:23.423
I'll bring him back
in one piece, Rosie.

04:24.891 --> 04:26.691
Okay.

04:40.340 --> 04:41.906
I'm trudging back up
the hill,

04:41.908 --> 04:43.206
and I'm cursing my back.

04:43.208 --> 04:44.508
I'm cursing my feet.

04:44.510 --> 04:45.876
I'm cursing all
of goddamn humanity,

04:45.878 --> 04:49.413
and then it hit me.

04:49.415 --> 04:50.881
The whole thing.

04:50.883 --> 04:55.586
So I sat down at my desk,
and two hours later...

04:55.588 --> 04:59.790
the most reviled story "The
New Yorker" has ever printed.

04:59.792 --> 05:04.428
I read it as
an anti-Semitic parable

05:04.430 --> 05:07.230
in the tradition of Isaac Babel.

05:07.232 --> 05:11.201
Calling my wife an Anti-Semite,
are we?

05:11.203 --> 05:14.605
Well, to be fair,
she never hated a single Jew

05:14.607 --> 05:16.540
until she married me.

05:17.744 --> 05:20.911
We had a wonderful courtship.

05:20.913 --> 05:22.278
Didn't we, dear?

05:22.280 --> 05:24.615
He asked me out
for cheeseburgers.

05:24.617 --> 05:26.784
Who could refuse such a...

05:26.786 --> 05:28.753
such a romance?

05:31.289 --> 05:34.558
Next thing I know, he's ripping
apart a story of mine.

05:34.560 --> 05:39.295
Then he has the gall to tell me
that he has lost his wallet.

05:41.334 --> 05:42.900
That wallet's been lost
for over 20 years.

05:44.437 --> 05:47.605
Now, mind you, that story...

05:47.607 --> 05:51.609
was the most remarkable story
I'd ever read.

05:51.611 --> 05:56.279
I knew I was going to marry
the woman who wrote it.

05:56.281 --> 06:00.685
I was going to hunt her down
and make her marry me.

06:00.687 --> 06:05.523
To our suffering, my dear.

06:05.525 --> 06:08.426
There's not enough Scotch
in the world for that one.

06:09.629 --> 06:12.331
So, Shirley,
what are you writing now?

06:19.605 --> 06:22.940
A little novella I'm calling
"None of Your Goddamn Business."

06:27.580 --> 06:31.517
Excuse me, I'm Rose.
Rose Nemser.

06:35.421 --> 06:37.988
Betty, Debbie, Kathy...

06:37.990 --> 06:39.623
You're all the same to me.

06:39.625 --> 06:41.992
No, no. I'm Fred's wife.
Fred Nemser.

06:41.994 --> 06:44.328
He's helping Professor Hyman
with this semester.

06:44.330 --> 06:47.631
We were invited to stay here
for a few days

06:47.633 --> 06:49.635
until we could find a place.

06:59.545 --> 07:01.647
No one said you were pregnant.

07:04.050 --> 07:06.853
W-We weren't telling
anybody yet.

07:11.958 --> 07:13.657
I-I-I read your story.

07:13.659 --> 07:14.692
There have been several.

07:14.694 --> 07:17.762
"The Lottery."

07:17.764 --> 07:20.433
When I read it,
it made me feel...

07:23.035 --> 07:24.804
...thrillingly horrible.

08:29.836 --> 08:31.669
♪ Father, did you bring me
the silver? ♪

08:31.671 --> 08:33.404
♪ Father, did you bring me
the gold? ♪

08:34.841 --> 08:36.642
That was Lead Belly.

08:39.611 --> 08:41.614
Huddie Ledbetter.

08:44.817 --> 08:48.452
This is Myth and Folklore.

08:48.454 --> 08:50.187
I am Professor Stanley Hyman,

08:50.189 --> 08:53.591
your fearless leader
for the next 12 weeks

08:53.593 --> 08:57.862
as we ascend to the heights
of the gods

08:57.864 --> 09:01.932
and stoop to the very depths
of human depravity.

09:03.035 --> 09:04.535
- Oh.
- Hello.

09:04.537 --> 09:06.971
Hi.
Isn't he great?

09:06.973 --> 09:09.073
Oh, terrific.
I wish my Chaucer class

09:09.075 --> 09:10.875
that I'm auditing wasn't
at the same time.

09:10.877 --> 09:13.777
Oh, well, there will be
other semesters.

09:13.779 --> 09:15.779
Sure.

09:15.781 --> 09:17.615
Might I burden you
with a favor?

09:17.617 --> 09:19.518
Hmm. What's that?

09:23.222 --> 09:26.156
Shirley has these bouts...

09:26.158 --> 09:28.993
and just can't, uh...

09:28.995 --> 09:30.628
can't keep up...

09:30.630 --> 09:32.930
with the household, shopping,

09:32.932 --> 09:35.499
and our last housekeeper
just quit.

09:35.501 --> 09:36.567
Oh.

09:36.569 --> 09:38.903
Bad back or lungs.

09:38.905 --> 09:41.772
I don't recall.
Maybe gout?

09:41.774 --> 09:44.208
But it would be such
a titanic help

09:44.210 --> 09:47.745
if you would just tidy up a bit.
Excuse me?

09:47.747 --> 09:48.946
Maybe chip in
with the laundry...

09:48.948 --> 09:51.615
- Yes?
- ...the cooking?

09:51.617 --> 09:53.884
- Oh...
- Well, no, no, no.

09:53.886 --> 09:55.920
That's too much.

09:55.922 --> 09:57.922
Don't think I confuse you
for a scullery maid.

09:57.924 --> 10:00.257
It's just, we are
in a bit of a bind.

10:00.259 --> 10:01.825
Well, perhaps I could...

10:01.827 --> 10:03.928
I could help out
in between classes?

10:03.930 --> 10:05.863
Well, obviously, room
and board on us.

10:05.865 --> 10:07.731
- Oh, no, no, no. We couldn't.
- No, no, no. Of course.

10:07.733 --> 10:09.066
- We couldn't.
- Of course. I insist.

10:09.068 --> 10:10.501
Might you stay, hmm?

10:10.503 --> 10:13.938
Just until we're...

10:13.940 --> 10:15.508
settled in, hmm?

10:20.079 --> 10:22.880
How's your rump roast?

10:22.882 --> 10:25.518
I love hot food in hot weather.

10:34.560 --> 10:36.694
He really seems in a bind.

10:36.696 --> 10:39.198
It could be sort of fun, hmm?

10:42.902 --> 10:44.704
Or we say no.

12:05.084 --> 12:07.618
♪ I like your walk ♪

12:09.188 --> 12:12.856
♪ Your simple ways ♪

12:12.858 --> 12:16.327
♪ A million things
about you, honey ♪

12:16.329 --> 12:20.130
♪ I could praise ♪

12:20.132 --> 12:24.402
♪ 'Cause everything
about you ♪

12:26.005 --> 12:29.807
♪ Appeals to me ♪

12:29.809 --> 12:31.975
I'm counting down from three.

12:35.714 --> 12:39.183
3... 2... 1.

12:47.360 --> 12:49.295
Get dressed for dinner,
darling.

12:51.297 --> 12:53.831
Please.

12:53.833 --> 12:57.835
Try.
Go away.

12:57.837 --> 13:00.003
I really think the two of them
are gonna work out.

13:00.005 --> 13:02.440
Did you see our kitchen?

13:02.442 --> 13:07.111
A clean house is evidence
of mental inferiority.

13:07.113 --> 13:08.846
Well, thank God
for the simpletons.

13:08.848 --> 13:11.115
How else would we ever
have fresh linens?

13:11.117 --> 13:13.851
You hired spies, is that it?

13:13.853 --> 13:15.686
I'm trying to help you,
Shirl.

13:15.688 --> 13:19.022
Take some of the pressure off
so you can get your work done.

13:19.024 --> 13:23.461
I don't want strangers here.
I don't like them.

13:23.463 --> 13:25.731
We've already discussed it,
dear.

13:28.834 --> 13:30.636
Hmm?

13:33.072 --> 13:34.805
Fred's going to lighten
my class load

13:34.807 --> 13:38.976
so that I can be
around the house more.

13:38.978 --> 13:40.478
Won't you like that?

13:45.951 --> 13:48.085
You can't expect me
to indulge this, can you?

13:48.087 --> 13:50.921
Hmm?

13:50.923 --> 13:53.056
Staying in bed all day?

13:53.058 --> 13:56.293
Well, the party was too much.
It set me back.

13:56.295 --> 13:58.962
You have to get back
to your desk.

13:58.964 --> 14:01.031
You're putting an undue
amount of pressure on me.

14:01.033 --> 14:03.368
Fussing over you
when I have work to do.

14:03.370 --> 14:05.938
You don't want my work
to suffer, too, do you?

14:09.074 --> 14:10.809
No.

14:24.089 --> 14:25.858
I'm going to get better.

14:28.093 --> 14:29.927
I promise.

14:29.929 --> 14:31.130
I will.

14:38.405 --> 14:41.406
Starting tomorrow.
No, starting tonight.

14:41.408 --> 14:43.807
You are putting on
clean clothes

14:43.809 --> 14:46.944
and sitting at the table
for a proper meal.

14:46.946 --> 14:49.213
- I can't.
- You will.

14:49.215 --> 14:50.983
Besides...

14:53.085 --> 14:54.851
...it's cocktail hour.

14:54.853 --> 14:57.122
Up, up, up.

15:00.493 --> 15:02.159
It's going to be so dull.

15:02.161 --> 15:06.131
Well, I didn't ask you
to behave at the table.

15:18.411 --> 15:20.411
Ooh, hoo, hoo, hoo.

15:20.413 --> 15:22.513
Oh, a gorgeous slab of flesh.

15:22.515 --> 15:24.848
Oh, it was nothing.

15:26.986 --> 15:29.186
Oh, go on, my boy.
Shed a layer.

15:29.188 --> 15:31.221
We aren't formal in this house.

15:31.223 --> 15:35.225
I've often thought
about participating

15:35.227 --> 15:38.396
in the Native American ritual
of the sweat lodge.

15:38.398 --> 15:40.831
- Thank you.
- Often?

15:40.833 --> 15:42.467
Why, yes, dear.

15:42.469 --> 15:46.003
But then I learned you have to
crawl through a dirt tunnel

15:46.005 --> 15:47.472
under the ground

15:47.474 --> 15:50.040
and sit naked buttocks
to naked buttocks

15:50.042 --> 15:53.043
with a dozen other men
while some shaman

15:53.045 --> 15:57.314
stokes a smoky fire, maintaining
the 100-degree heat

15:57.316 --> 16:01.051
and peddles some noxious
root tea

16:01.053 --> 16:03.186
that inspires hallucinations.

16:03.188 --> 16:04.323
Ooh!

16:15.267 --> 16:18.336
So when's the baby due?

16:18.338 --> 16:20.237
- The baby?
- Oops.

16:20.239 --> 16:21.606
Was it supposed to be
a surprise?

16:21.608 --> 16:25.208
You should have
told me that, dear.

16:25.210 --> 16:26.877
Well, I hope it's yours.

16:26.879 --> 16:29.212
Of course it's his.

16:29.214 --> 16:32.182
February. Hmm.
Right, darling?

16:32.184 --> 16:34.017
I would really rather discuss
something else,

16:34.019 --> 16:36.286
if you don't mind.
February? Ha.

16:36.288 --> 16:39.258
Did you tell him you were
knocked up before the wedding?

16:42.027 --> 16:44.261
I fear, my love,
stories of copulations

16:44.263 --> 16:47.498
might leave the table
without an appetite,

16:47.500 --> 16:51.636
but that one does have
a sixth sense about babies.

16:51.638 --> 16:54.672
Calls it. Girl or a boy,
she's never wrong.

16:54.674 --> 16:57.240
Is poor Freddie here
going to be disappointed?

17:13.359 --> 17:15.125
Okay. Shall I...?

17:15.127 --> 17:16.862
Stay put.

17:18.964 --> 17:20.698
You promised
to take care of that.

17:24.637 --> 17:27.571
As you wish, dear.

17:31.243 --> 17:34.379
So, Rose, you were telling us
about your shotgun wedding.

17:35.515 --> 17:38.416
Excuse me.

17:38.418 --> 17:41.920
I should see
if she's all right.

17:50.363 --> 17:53.932
I feel a bit like
we're in the Scottish play.

17:55.702 --> 17:59.437
I, the Thane of Cawdor,

17:59.439 --> 18:03.474
with a murderous prophecy
over my head.

18:03.476 --> 18:08.178
And you, Lady M...

18:08.180 --> 18:10.548
on the verge of madness.

18:10.550 --> 18:13.686
What will happen?

18:22.294 --> 18:23.561
I have a title.

18:23.563 --> 18:25.228
"Hangsaman."

18:25.230 --> 18:27.365
It's about that girl.

18:27.367 --> 18:28.566
The missing one.

18:28.568 --> 18:30.334
The Welden girl?

18:30.336 --> 18:32.002
What do you think?

18:32.004 --> 18:35.305
Well, you haven't said much.

18:35.307 --> 18:37.542
Well, it's just an idea.

18:37.544 --> 18:41.111
I can try something else.
Disappearing college girls.

18:41.113 --> 18:45.148
Sounds trite and a bit trashy,
but, you know, give it a go.

18:45.150 --> 18:48.352
I'll read, of course,
before you wade too far in.

18:48.354 --> 18:50.287
It's going to take some time.

18:50.289 --> 18:52.255
Well, give it to me
in a couple of days.

18:52.257 --> 18:55.426
It's a novel.

18:55.428 --> 18:58.763
Oh, no, dear.
That's...

18:58.765 --> 19:01.632
You're not...

19:01.634 --> 19:03.403
You're just not up to it.

19:05.472 --> 19:07.538
You're wrong.

19:07.540 --> 19:11.109
Darling, you haven't been out
of the house in two months.

19:13.078 --> 19:16.614
You're barely able to put
on a pair of stockings.

19:16.616 --> 19:19.151
Ease back.
That's all I'm saying.

19:24.791 --> 19:27.391
If that phone rings...

19:27.393 --> 19:30.595
one more time during dinner...

19:30.597 --> 19:34.264
Stanley, so help me, I'm going
to take care of it myself.

19:34.266 --> 19:36.400
I'm well within the bounds
of our agreement.

19:36.402 --> 19:38.469
Ah. Hmm.

19:38.471 --> 19:44.009
Our agreement didn't include
sluts interrupting my dinner.

19:45.812 --> 19:48.679
I will talk to her

19:48.681 --> 19:52.084
and tell you everything,
as I always do.

19:55.287 --> 19:57.622
You're really scraping
the barrel these days.

